Three COVID-19 patients have been discharged in Kano State. The coordinator of the Technical Response Team on COVID-19, Dr Tijjani Hussain, who disclosed this said the patients were discharged after testing negative twice to the virus. Hussain disclosed this during a briefing by the state’s task force. Recall that Kano had recently recorded twenty-three new cases of COVID-19 as was confirmed by the states Ministry of Health. A tweet on the ministry’s official account confirmed a total of 365 cases and eight deaths currently.